text: Part of what makes the first 100k tougher is you're new. I made rookie mistakes (dividend investing) the first year or two, and investing wasn't as routine. It took over 3 years to hit 100k, cheerfully accepting 10% returns. The 2nd 100k took a little over a year once I switched to growth stocks. Once you're getting good returns, you start throwing everything at it. Get a bonus? Invest it. Get a raise? Invest it. Tax refund? Invest it. Fiancee returns your ring? Invest it. ;-)
